{
  "texts": [
    "Due to the structure that embeds into primary model architecture, fidelity score may not require a thorough examination for intrinsic interpretation methods.",
    "However, it is required for post-hoc methods because their function of interpretation frequently differs from the primary model architecture [159].",
    "Fidelity score is calculated by dividing the number of samples in the dataset by the ratio of correct explanation c of black-box b for the dataset c(x) = b(x), for (x, ŷ) ∈ D test.",
    "It can also be measured using common accuracy scores like F1-score and recall [85,152].",
    "Factors influencing the effectiveness of concept-supported XAIBased to the literature, conceptual interpretation methods can significantly contribute to closing the gap between advanced black-box models and human rational thinking."
  ]
}